  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group international cooperation standards\n\n2. Domestic Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (in the UK)\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance\n- Financial institutions must implement AML programs\n- Regular reporting to government authorities\n- Internal control mechanisms\n\n5. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Professional license revocation\n\n6. Investigative Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Specialized financial crime units\n\n7. Preventive Measures\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Risk-based assessment approaches\n- Enhanced due diligence for high-risk transactions\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes.",
